# 9. Slow Timing Scan

## Objective

Reduce the likelihood of IDS detection.

## Command

```bash
sudo nmap -T2 <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
sudo nmap -T2 <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/timing-scan.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-T2` uses a polite timing template.
- Sends packets more slowly.
- Helps avoid triggering IDS/IPS systems.
- Increases scan duration.

